{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"499c","heading":"Portfolio management framework for nuclear forces","label":"499c Portfolio management framework for nuclear forces","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/stA/ptI/ch24","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":".—Requirement","label":"a .—Requirement","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"specifies the portfolio of nuclear forces covered by the framework;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"establishes a portfolio governance structure for such forces that takes advantage of, or is modeled on, an existing portfolio governance structure, such as the Deputy’s Management Action Group described in Department of Defense Directive 5105.79;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fa%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"outlines the approach of the Secretary for identifying and managing risk relating to such forces and prioritizing the efforts among such forces, including how the Secretary, acting through the Under Secretary of Defense for Acquisition and Sustainment, will coordinate such identification, management, and prioritization with the Administrator for Nuclear Security using the coordination processes of the Nuclear Weapons Council; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fa%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"incorporates the findings and recommendations identified by the Comptroller General of the United States in the report titled “Nuclear Enterprise: DOD and NNSA Could Further Enhance How They Manage Risk and Prioritize Efforts” (GAO–22–104061) and dated January 2022; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"complete a comprehensive assessment of the portfolio management capabilities required to identify and manage risk in the portfolio of nuclear forces, including how to draw upon public and private sector resources and the program management expertise within the Defense Acquisition University.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":".—Annual Briefings; Notifications","label":"b .—Annual Briefings; Notifications","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the current and projected operational requirements for nuclear forces that were used for such identification, management, and prioritization;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"key areas of risk identified; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fb%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of the actions proposed or carried out to mitigate such risk.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Secretary may provide the briefings under paragraph (1) in classified form.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"If a House of Congress adopts a bill authorizing or appropriating funds that, as determined by the Secretary, provides funds in an amount that will result in a significant delay in the nuclear certification or delivery of nuclear forces, the Secretary shall notify the congressional defense committees of the determination.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":".—Termination","label":"c .—Termination","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The LGM–35A Sentinel intercontinental ballistic missile weapon system.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Columbia-class ballistic missile submarine program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The long-range standoff weapon program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The B–21 Raider bomber aircraft program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fc%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The F–35A dual-capable aircraft program.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":".—Nuclear Forces Defined","label":"d .—Nuclear Forces Defined","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"nuclear weapons;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the delivery platforms and systems for nuclear weapons;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/d/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fd%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"nuclear command, control, and communications systems; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/d/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t10/s499c/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft10%2Fs499c%2Fd%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the infrastructure and facilities of the Department of Defense and the National Nuclear Security Administration that support nuclear weapons, the delivery platforms and systems for nuclear weapons, and nuclear command, control, and communications systems, including with respect to personnel, construction, operation, and maintenance.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
